reviewText:
aRPGs are not my cup of tea but I remembered watching a review of it when it was in Early Access, got it on a whim and it's a decision I don't regret. It's fast-paced, beautiful and the sound track is awesome. It's a solid 5/7.

Pros:
- people with arachnophobia get to kill a lot of spiders;
- you get stuff when you level up. Not always useful, but stuff. More often than not it is useful, though, and if you don't like it, you can sell it;
- you can jump and uncover secrets this way (be weary of conspicuously placed pillars), dodge enemy ranged attacks by jumping over the projectiles, navigate some mazes a lot easier;
- the narrator. You will either love him or hate him. Just the right amount of sass for my taste, reminded me of the one in The Stanley Parable.
- because Victor Vran is Victor Vran and not each players rendition of Victor Vran or Viktoria Vranovskaya, the trans-gender bearded female version whom they decided to make wear a skirt, you can jump right in once the quick download is finished (~3.5 Gb, I think, for the ones who are still on a plan);
- quick transitions to and from the keep where the base is located;
- next to no loading times (literally, <1s on a decent but by no means fancy gaming PC, not installed on SSD);
- overkill mechanic is an interesting concept that I haven't seen before - I didn't really play a lot of aRPGs so that may be why;
- good humor;
- control is spot on using both keyboard + mouse and controller;
- Private Stash (you'll know it when you see it).

Cons:
- people with arachnophobia get to see a lot of spiders;
- caught a few glitches when entering dialogues with the NPCs where the screen froze for half a second - not every time, noticeable but not really disturbing;
- only happened once so far but the game would not let me jump off of a platform to a different lower level unless I did it  from a specific spot.
- story line does not feel engaging - but story line should not be why you buy an aRPG after all

Final score, based totally on whatever I feel like, would be an 83/100 or even an 8.3/10. I would have liked to see just a sliver more on the story side.
